# Unique Page Imagery Requirement

- For every net-new page, generate unique AI images specific to that page's topic and content.
- Never use stock imagery libraries (Unsplash, Pexels, Shutterstock, etc.) for page visuals.
- Never use SVGs as image placeholders for page content.
- Do not copy or reuse image URLs from an existing route into a new route.
- The correct workflow for new page images:
  1. Generate AI images using the GenerateImage tool with page-specific, on-brand prompts
  2. Upload each image to the client's Supabase `site-assets/images/` bucket using the service role key
  3. Reference the resulting `https://<ref>.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/site-assets/images/<filename>` URL in the page
- Name image files consistently: `<route-prefix>_<section><index>.jpg` (e.g. `wt_ptsd_hero01.jpg`)
- Write alt text that is specific to the page's clinical/topic context, not generic boilerplate.
- Reuse an existing image only when the user explicitly approves an exception.
